Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.91,0:28:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.23,0:29:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I was brought up very religious, about as religious as you can get.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.60,0:29:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I went.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.80,0:29:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I went through a period of disillusionment
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.25,0:29:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and became a dedicated atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.55,0:29:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,First a dedicated religionist, then a dedicated atheist,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.05,0:29:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,then a dedicated agnostic.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.52,0:29:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, they say atheism was naive, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.33,0:29:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Agnostic was more sophisticated.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.59,0:29:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't prove the existence of God one way or the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.59,0:29:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't say God doesn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.11,0:29:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.21,0:29:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can just say I, of myself, am unable to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.32,0:29:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So where is agnosticism?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.75,0:29:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Agnostic on this thing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.77,0:29:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.25,0:29:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.05,0:29:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not even on there.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.83,0:29:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not called an enlightened state.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.55,0:29:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called an intellectually sophisticated state.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.79,0:29:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So the agnostic, then, represents intellectual sophistication
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.20,0:29:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that you've thought about the subject
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.61,0:29:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and realized that the mind alone is unable to solve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.21,0:30:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So the agnostic is integrous
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.69,0:30:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and that he realizes the limitation of the human intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.75,0:30:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,In and of itself, it's not a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.76,0:30:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.84,0:30:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.95,0:30:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.00,0:30:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.10,0:30:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.13,0:30:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,In and of itself cannot handle the cushion
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.67,0:30:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,of the infinite non-linear domain of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.28,0:30:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.32,0:30:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It exists within it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.84,0:30:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So how can it answer it when it is within itself?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.39,0:30:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So the infinite realm of consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.28,0:30:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,with no beginning and no end
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.89,0:30:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is the source of infinite power.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.22,0:30:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,As we have said before,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.59,0:30:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,one cubic centimeter of empty space
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.61,0:30:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,has more transactions.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.05,0:30:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,intrinsic power within it than the mass of the entire universe. Those who are interested
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.18,0:30:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in the advances of scientific advances in consciousness, there's the new book by the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.42,0:31:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,professor of physics at Berkeley, whose name I always forget. What's his name? Henry Stapp.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.55,0:31:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I know. All right. Henry Stapp's new book called Mindful Universe integrates modern
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.66,0:31:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,science and consciousness in a very elegant way and is about as sophisticated as you need
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.11,0:31:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to get from a scientific viewpoint, yes? The enlightened divine states then, the supreme
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.99,0:31:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Godhead, these all calibrated at 1,000 or 5,000, and Archangel is 5,000 and up. Christ
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.96,0:31:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddha had, within this realm, the great avatars calibrated at 1,000. All these are
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.91,0:31:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the science and consciousness in a very elegant way and is about as sophisticated as you need
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.00,0:31:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to get.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.32,0:31:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the states about which man has wondered and written, and they're the most difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.66,0:32:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to define, because that which is called enlightenment is a nonlinear condition, and there's no one
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.51,0:32:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to whom it occurs, and there is no person who becomes enlightened. What happens is that
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.10,0:32:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,which is linear disappears, and the linear is replaced by the nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.76,0:32:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,by the nonlinear the nonlinear is a knowingness with neither subject nor
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.34,0:32:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,predicate nor adjective nor verb it's a state of being and awareness and it
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.08,0:32:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,exists in and of itself and it is not an attribute of any person so no person
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.66,0:32:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes enlightened what happens is that that which was is replaced by an
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.38,0:32:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite state so the what exists then is this is an infinite state in the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.36,0:33:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,service of which the body speaks and walks around etc and this condition
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.95,0:33:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,comes on unwittingly of its own and there's certain karmic propensities and
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.41,0:33:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of course the spiritual work what we try to do is remove the obstacles so we
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.19,0:33:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,don't create an enlightened state we don't create an enlightened state what
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.04,0:33:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,happens is we remove the obstacles and when you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.84,0:33:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,remove the obstacles you don't create an enlightened state and when you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.89,0:33:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,remove the obstacles which is the purpose that we were talking today when
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.86,0:33:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you remove the obstacles then the state it prevails of its own and you really
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.21,0:33:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,recognize that it's there and that it's been there all along ordinarily what you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.07,0:33:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,do is you begin to eliminate all conceptual thought all conceptual
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.96,0:33:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,thought why because conceptual thought all has to do with appearance and
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.56,0:33:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,reality has to do with essence
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.21,0:33:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,well we calibrate something what are we we're at what we're asking is what is
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.77,0:34:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,this it's it's absolute reality what is the essence not the appearance so we know
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.11,0:34:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,what appearance looks like it looks like uh uh the blog blogger world what do
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.07,0:34:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,they call the blogger world internet bloggerism whatever that is it shatters
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.78,0:34:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the way about appearance you know it goes from ridiculous to absurd to some sometimes
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.94,0:34:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,it's factually accurate but what it's talking about is what a thing appears uh to be Nancy
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.21,0:34:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the former president's wife who was in feeble condition you know and then the internet came
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.51,0:34:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,on saying things that were so spectacularly horrible you can't believe they were said
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.28,0:34:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and then suddenly they disappeared so at least there's a bit of sanity left someplace
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.86,0:34:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to say such wicked things about people you know all right so appearance then has nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.05,0:35:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to do with reality and we what we try to teach you in these classes is the difference between
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.90,0:35:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,appearance and essence what a thing looks like and what it is are two widely divergent things
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.32,0:35:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and frankly without calibrating the level of Consciousness uh very often it's impossible to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.32,0:35:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to tell whether a thing is true or not true and uh everybody can put their hand on a stack of Bibles
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.86,0:35:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and then lie done in court every day
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.28,0:35:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,done in court every day put your hand in the Bible you're sorry I do then they get up and they lie
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.96,0:35:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that would scare the wits out of me what it was imagine your left final moments on left you're
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.42,0:35:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,going to meet God in a couple of seconds and you think of all the stuff you swore was the truth on
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.23,0:35:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bible say sorry God I take that all back I take that all back Lord yeah so we can verify that
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.84,0:35:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,which is not
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.80,0:36:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,accessible to the ordinary human mind and the human mind deals in the linear world of logic
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.86,0:36:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and reason in addition to feelings so between feeling and logic and reason it then reaches its
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.36,0:36:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,limit from that point on then what's what prevails is the field of Consciousness itself it's because
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.55,0:36:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of uh Consciousness we have awareness and because of awareness we're able to discern reality so these
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.92,0:36:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,are the supreme
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.82,0:36:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,states that we calibrated very earlier in this work and uh the purpose was to see these run from 600
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.78,0:36:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and up so the Enlightened States calibrate level 600 and up uh the Satchitananda begins at 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.82,0:37:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the state does not announce itself a state of Bliss takes over a state of completeness at level 600. so
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.73,0:37:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual students are aiming at least for this this is a a doable reachable state
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.17,0:37:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,where you let go all the negatives and surrender them all to Divinity you stop listening to the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.57,0:37:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,mind and propagating conceptual thinking and you focus and then pray uh to God to understand the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.42,0:37:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,essence of the essence of Divinity the essence of love and then in one happy moment with karmic uh
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.59,0:37:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,propensities prevail the state emerges of its own people get close to it sometimes with very
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.09,0:37:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,beautiful music very beautiful music can bring you very close to beatific states which uh with
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.76,0:37:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,some practice you can turn slowly turn off the music and the state will continue the state will
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.67,0:38:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,continue of its own without being propped up by the music although the music will certainly set
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.40,0:38:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in the right dimension, the right mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.98,0:38:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The music we see on Channel 8, for instance,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.03,0:38:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the beatific music we were listening to
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.55,0:38:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,was over 600, 700, 650.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.69,0:38:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so the beautiful music
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.42,0:38:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you see on Channel 8 recently,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.59,0:38:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,PBS station calibrated the music itself
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.86,0:38:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,at 650, Celtic Woman and what was the other one?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.94,0:38:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Celtic Woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.84,0:38:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Celtic Woman, yes, and the great tenors, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.55,0:38:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, Greek classical music
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.25,0:38:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,will lift you all the way to 700.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.28,0:38:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So there is a crossover.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.94,0:38:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't get to the 600s or 700s through thinking this,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.36,0:38:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,so reading a book isn't going to get you there.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.88,0:38:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So what would give you a sense of what it's like?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.40,0:38:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The sense of what it's like
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.65,0:39:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,is you're walking through the woods
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.05,0:39:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and you completely forget about time or place
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.19,0:39:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're like,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.51,0:39:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and the infinite silence of the wood is enchanting
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.03,0:39:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,or an infinitely beautiful music that makes you cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.32,0:39:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The kind of beautiful music that makes you cry
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.50,0:39:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's so incredibly beautiful
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.23,0:39:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is bringing you very close to that divine state
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.03,0:39:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's letting you know that that divine state is available
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.17,0:39:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and that you can experience the same state
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.76,0:39:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,without the prop of music itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.28,0:39:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But I think great music.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.38,0:39:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So we know that great music,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.51,0:39:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,especially in childhood,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.51,0:39:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,has a profoundly positive experience
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.51,0:39:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,on the way your neurons connect
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.51,0:39:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.51,0:39:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiate later spiritual evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.51,0:39:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it was discovered that the neurons,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.63,0:39:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, the neurons proliferate
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.63,0:39:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,at a greater rate than they're needed
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.63,0:39:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and the excess are trimmed out.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.63,0:39:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it's been discovered in recent decades
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.46,0:40:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that the creation of new neurons
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.46,0:40:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore to be connected in the right brain,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.46,0:40:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,continues on into age, age, the older you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.46,0:40:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So even though you're 70 or 80,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.46,0:40:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,your mind is still proliferating new neurons
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.46,0:40:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can still learn things
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.46,0:40:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that you failed to learn when you were young.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.50,0:40:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It was thought before that unless you learned it
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.50,0:40:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,when you were young, you know, you would never learn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.50,0:40:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So we find that the same things that propitiate
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.78,0:40:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,or potentiate spiritual comprehension and understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.78,0:40:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in youth continues to work into adulthood.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.78,0:40:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace and music and such things.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.78,0:40:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Great beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.78,0:40:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Great beauty potentiates it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.78,0:40:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The sensitivity, it isn't just the music,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.78,0:40:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,but the sensitivity to music.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.78,0:40:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've spoken over the years
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.98,0:40:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,about some of the kind of music
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.98,0:40:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that tends to bring tears to your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.98,0:40:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The kind of music that tends to bring tears to your eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.98,0:41:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is the kind that brings you closest to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.98,0:41:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.98,0:41:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll move to the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.53,0:41:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.53,0:41:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we had said...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.03,0:41:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Which slide was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.09,0:41:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We skipped one.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.09,0:41:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We went backwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.09,0:41:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.09,0:41:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where the world's population is, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.15,0:41:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We've shown these slides over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.15,0:41:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,85% of the world's population
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.26,0:41:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,lives below this critical level of 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.26,0:41:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That sort of modifies your expectations of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.59,0:41:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Your expectations of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.59,0:41:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the majority
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.59,0:41:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of the world's population, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.59,0:41:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is below the level of truth and integrity at 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.63,0:41:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You can sell them anything, and they'll buy anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.63,0:41:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and they'll kill you for any reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.63,0:41:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that sound pessimistic?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.63,0:41:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not pessimistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.63,0:41:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But limited.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.63,0:42:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But limited.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.44,0:42:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,When you ride the subways,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.44,0:42:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,keep your billfold where you know where it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.44,0:42:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just reality-oriented.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.67,0:42:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Reality-oriented, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.67,0:42:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.67,0:42:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So 85% of the world's population.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.67,0:42:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, an audience such as this is exceptional.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.67,0:42:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The chances of an audience like this being together
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.67,0:42:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,in one place in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.67,0:42:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,are practically zero, less than .0001% probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.67,0:42:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The chances are less than .0001%
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.67,0:42:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,for a congregation like this to assemble or exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.67,0:42:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Less than .0001% that's such a group of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.67,0:42:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, this group of people here
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.67,0:42:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is influencing the level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.67,0:42:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.67,0:42:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That is true, O Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.67,0:42:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This audience now, here assembled,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.30,0:43:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,here, right here, right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.94,0:43:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is profoundly affecting the level of mankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.50,0:43:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,profoundly affecting the level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.42,0:43:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.42,0:43:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.53,0:43:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That, indeed, is a gift and a responsibility, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.59,0:43:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That by virtue of that which you have become,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.19,0:43:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of that which you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.42,0:43:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,not by virtue of what you do or say,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.76,0:43:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of what you have become and what you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.98,0:43:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you're preventing the ship from sinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.50,0:43:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.50,0:43:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Just folks like you just breathing in and out
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.65,0:43:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is doing the whole universe a favor,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.65,0:43:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you understand what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.42,0:43:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,People always want to have a Save the Globe conference
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.42,0:44:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're going to have a parade in Central Park
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.42,0:44:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll have bands and flags and save the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.42,0:44:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Then they have the riot police, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.82,0:44:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't what you do, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.82,0:44:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,it's what you have become.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.01,0:44:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's by virtue of what you have become
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.01,0:44:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're profoundly influencing
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.01,0:44:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the consciousness level of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.78,0:44:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,To give up wickedness in all its ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.78,0:44:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.78,0:44:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Give up the devil and all his works.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.78,0:44:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.26,0:44:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,All we need is some kind of guidance to tell us
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.26,0:44:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,which way is the truth and which way is falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.26,0:44:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,which way is heaven,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.26,0:44:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,which way is hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.03,0:45:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to go and get a master's degree
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.03,0:45:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to figure that out, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.57,0:45:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But for 85% of the world's population, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.96,0:45:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,exists below level 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.96,0:45:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They are dedicated to falsehood and non-integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.38,0:45:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and dishonesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.38,0:45:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.80,0:45:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.61,0:45:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's move on to the next story.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.61,0:45:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, here, here's a different way of depicting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.61,0:45:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going over the basics this time
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.61,0:45:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,because we don't want to go through these basics again.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.61,0:45:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We want them so familiar you don't have to think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.75,0:45:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.75,0:45:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, a group like this is somewhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.82,0:45:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,a group like this is somewhere near the very top,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.82,0:45:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,peak of the, of the pyramid.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.82,0:45:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the greater, the farther consciousness has evolved,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.82,0:45:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the greater is its power.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.82,0:45:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't have to do anything to save the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.61,0:45:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Just be what you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.61,0:46:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,as loving and kind towards all of life as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.61,0:46:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.61,0:46:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,To be as loving and forgiving as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.61,0:46:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,To look at the negatives with a sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.61,0:46:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think one of the most powerful spiritual tools
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.61,0:46:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is a sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.61,0:46:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a sense of humor, you're not going to last long.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.51,0:46:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,A sense of humor, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.51,0:46:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is the capacity to look at the other side of a story,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.51,0:46:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.51,0:46:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,what could be termed depressing and reprehensible,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.51,0:46:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and be able to handle it and let it bounce off,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.51,0:46:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,let it bounce off yourself and say,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.51,0:46:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,yes, I know that exists in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.51,0:46:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just that I don't subscribe to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.57,0:46:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is a very profoundly important group of people here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.57,0:46:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,California is lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.92,0:46:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't this California?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.92,0:46:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This is California, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.01,0:46:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this California? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.01,0:47:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Hollywood. No, we're in Los Angeles.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.01,0:47:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Long Beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.46,0:47:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew we'd get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.46,0:47:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.46,0:47:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we did with the arm before,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.88,0:47:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,we said, what's happening with these people right here?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.30,0:47:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Because these people right here in this congregation right here
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.30,0:47:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,are really the tip, the tip.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.30,0:47:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.30,0:47:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And just by breathing in and out,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.30,0:47:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you see that you calibrate the great mass of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.38,0:47:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.63,0:47:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And you say, well,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.63,0:47:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,we don't notice that mankind is improving in many ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.05,0:47:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but what you do by just sitting there and breathing in and out
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.05,0:47:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,is you keep it from destroying itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.05,0:47:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't for a group like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.05,0:47:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind would have already destroyed itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.82,0:47:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Very close to it, flirts with it all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.82,0:47:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Nuclear bombs and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.01,0:47:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't for this group here,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.01,0:47:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind would probably have destroyed itself already, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.01,0:48:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.42,0:48:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we all should get some kind of a button.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.42,0:48:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I saved the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.42,0:48:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We could get a save the world card, official stamp on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.42,0:48:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I helped save the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.28,0:48:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,When you get to the pearly gates,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.28,0:48:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,St. Peter now has a computer, you understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.28,0:48:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And he looks up your card number.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.53,0:48:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, you may pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.94,0:48:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you racking up there, St. Peter?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.01,0:48:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got you on his computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.01,0:48:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So at this end, he says,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.36,0:48:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you can go that line over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.36,0:48:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,At this end, he says that you can stand in line on the other one.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.65,0:48:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, we'll go to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.65,0:48:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Just that we're familiar with these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.65,0:48:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolution of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.73,0:48:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I was mistaken on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.73,0:49:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought this is over elapsed time in the consciousness level.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.63,0:49:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You see it was rising up to what it was then.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.63,0:49:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,To what is called now.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.15,0:49:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought it was going to continue to go up.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.63,0:49:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.73,0:49:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It went up to 207 or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.73,0:49:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it curled around and came back to 204.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.73,0:49:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.07,0:49:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So that means the consciousness level can advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.07,0:49:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it can go down.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.07,0:49:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it can advance again and go down.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.07,0:49:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's not a straight linear progression.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.07,0:49:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And events on that level,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.07,0:49:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,events on the planet and man's reaction to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.36,0:49:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see what man is overall now.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.36,0:49:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to do man overall right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.42,0:49:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Mankind overall is over 204, 205, 204.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.03,0:49:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He was up to 207.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.03,0:49:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He was up to 207.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.73,0:49:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Mankind was up to 207.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.73,0:50:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Now he's down to the 204 again.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.73,0:50:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not working hard enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.28,0:50:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I've got to get more lectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.59,0:50:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.59,0:50:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the people that need to hear what we've got to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.90,0:50:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,they're not going to come to a lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.90,0:50:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all hogwash to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.67,0:50:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Goody, goody, two-shoes stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.67,0:50:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Be kind to your neighbor and all that jazz.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.03,0:50:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, if he doesn't agree with you, be at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.03,0:50:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I say.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.03,0:50:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Chop him some off.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.03,0:50:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,There.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.03,0:50:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That solves the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.34,0:50:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But be good-natured about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.88,0:50:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the guillotine when we need it, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.84,0:50:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The guillotine chopped off 15,000 heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.84,0:50:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, that's a lot of work, wouldn't you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.84,0:50:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Fifteen thousand people got beheaded by the guillotine
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.84,0:50:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in the name of freedom and democracy.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.34,0:50:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.53,0:51:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Fifteen thousand people, the guillotine.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.53,0:51:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.40,0:51:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Earth epics and calibrated levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.40,0:51:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This can't be seen very easily from this audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.40,0:51:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one reason we're going to put all these charts out
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.40,0:51:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in a book form or some available form,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.40,0:51:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,because these can't really be seen from the seats.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.40,0:51:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But all it shows is that the level of the energy of life itself
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.40,0:51:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,on the planet has evolved over great eons of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.40,0:51:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It began at calibrated level of one, bacteria, algae,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.40,0:51:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,first signs of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.40,0:51:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the invertebrates,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.40,0:51:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated level of eight.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.40,0:51:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the fish, first traces of land life.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.40,0:51:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see how the calibrated level of life on this planet
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.40,0:51:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,over the great ages slowly evolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.59,0:52:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The ages of the dinosaur, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.59,0:52:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,How life itself is evolutionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.59,0:52:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So life itself is evolutionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.07,0:52:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We're evolutionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.07,0:52:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Life is evolutionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.07,0:52:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Mankind is evolutionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.36,0:52:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So that takes care of the evolution versus creation argument.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.46,0:52:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Because man was created in an evolutionary pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.53,0:52:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So the creation is that, you know, God was,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.53,0:52:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind was created by God.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.61,0:52:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So the trouble with the evolutionists,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.61,0:52:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the radical evolutionists,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.61,0:52:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is they think the world is only 6,000 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.61,0:52:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So they don't make much sense at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.61,0:52:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Man was created to be evolutionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.44,0:52:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's no conflict between creation and evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.44,0:52:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Because man was created to be evolutionary,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.44,0:52:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to learn, to grow, to evolve,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.44,0:52:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to fulfill his potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.50,0:52:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.50,0:52:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And to fly to the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.50,0:53:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Fly to the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.50,0:53:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, that's the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.50,0:53:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the animal kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.50,0:53:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,which we touch upon because, again,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.50,0:53:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,it tends to cement these things in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.59,0:53:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We have the dog's wagging tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.73,0:53:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We did,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.73,0:53:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,we did our new dog,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.73,0:53:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,a new dog at 250,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.73,0:53:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,55.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.76,0:53:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the family dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.76,0:53:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The family dog is 250.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.76,0:53:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.76,0:53:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,this dog, Kelsey, is at 255.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.78,0:53:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we notice we have a
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.88,0:53:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,gray parrot at home, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.94,0:53:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have a trained gorilla.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.94,0:53:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd like to have one.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.26,0:53:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Susan said, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.26,0:53:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.26,0:53:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.42,0:53:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.42,0:53:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.42,0:53:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No trained gorilla?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.86,0:53:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.86,0:53:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We also have three cats
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.86,0:53:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and a dog's wagging tail now.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.86,0:53:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So three cats purring at 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.86,0:54:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And a dog's wagging tail wagging at 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.86,0:54:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And a bird,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.86,0:54:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,a bird singing and talking at 405.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.86,0:54:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see why things are pretty good around the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.86,0:54:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to stay mad at anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.86,0:54:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to stay mad at anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.86,0:54:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if the bird doesn't get you,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.86,0:54:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the bird gives our phone number out to everybody,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.86,0:54:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,answers the phone,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.21,0:54:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and makes a click like it's hanging up.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.21,0:54:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.21,0:54:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,2-8-2-4-4-6-9.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.21,0:54:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.50,0:54:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the parrot talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.55,0:54:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The kitty is purring around your legs,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.55,0:54:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,wanting attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.55,0:54:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And the doggie comes over and puts his head on your lap
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.55,0:54:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and says,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.88,0:54:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So that represents the world
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.92,0:54:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can create for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.92,0:54:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.05,0:54:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The world you create for yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.05,0:54:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is one of love and affection.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.26,0:54:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So the way to enlightenment is
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.26,0:55:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to be loving towards all of life
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.61,0:55:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.61,0:55:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,To be unconditionally loving towards all of life
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.61,0:55:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and all its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.61,0:55:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,To be loving means also to make allowance for limitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.61,0:55:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And that can't really be done without humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.61,0:55:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way you can handle
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.61,0:55:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,some of the extreme negatives of life
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.61,0:55:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,without humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.61,0:55:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So humor is a spiritual tool,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.61,0:55:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,one that's underrepresented
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.61,0:55:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world's great religions.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.98,0:55:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You seem so grim about everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.98,0:55:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.98,0:55:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.98,0:55:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Crack a smile would kill him,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.98,0:55:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.63,0:55:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a sense of humor, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.07,0:55:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll have a hard time maintaining spiritual principles.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.07,0:55:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you remain loving towards life
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.07,0:55:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,when you see some of the absurdities that go on
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.07,0:55:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and represent the ultimate cruelty
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.07,0:55:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and sadism, et cetera?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.07,0:56:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the last thing we need to save our sanity, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.13,0:56:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is an explanation for those things
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.13,0:56:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that cannot be handled by humor, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.13,0:56:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, an understanding of karma
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.13,0:56:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is essential, I think,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.13,0:56:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to serious spiritual students.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.13,0:56:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there's no other way
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.13,0:56:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you contextualize things that are inexplicable
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.13,0:56:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that happen to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.26,0:56:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be the most saintly person on the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.26,0:56:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and get run over by a cab.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.32,0:56:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,She's on their way to help the poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.32,0:56:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Bags of food and money and medicine
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.00,0:56:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for the sick, sick children.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.00,0:56:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Armloads of sick children medicine
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.32,0:56:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and the taxi cab.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.09,0:56:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Get off the straight, Joe Krohn.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.78,0:56:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you explain that?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.88,0:57:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So the last thing we need, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.13,0:57:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to fit it all together,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.13,0:57:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the calibrated levels of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.13,0:57:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the awareness that the brain
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.13,0:57:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is constantly proliferating neurons,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.13,0:57:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore you can become more spiritually adept
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.13,0:57:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the older you get,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.13,0:57:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,which is contrary to what people used to think.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.76,0:57:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you add the understanding of karma,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.76,0:57:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you've got all that you need.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.76,0:57:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't really become enlightened
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.96,0:57:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,without understanding karma,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.96,0:57:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and my understanding of it, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.96,0:57:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Because how would you handle
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.96,0:57:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,all the negatives?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.96,0:57:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you'd say, what is that,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.96,0:57:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,God's punishment for wickedness?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.96,0:57:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, how do you handle that stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.96,0:57:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So without a sense of humor, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.01,0:57:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.01,0:57:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And the answer, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.73,0:57:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,it comes from the teachings of the Buddha
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.73,0:57:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and karma, Hindu,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.73,0:57:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and comes from the Eastern cultures,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.75,0:57:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,an understanding of karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.75,0:57:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can use, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.75,0:57:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness calibration to confirm,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.75,0:57:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is karma a valid reality?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.75,0:57:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.75,0:58:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask this.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.75,0:58:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Karma is a valid reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.75,0:58:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.75,0:58:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,A valid, confirmable reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.75,0:58:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.75,0:58:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.75,0:58:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.75,0:58:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.94,0:58:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So then you have the last spiritual tool you need.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.03,0:58:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't really handle spiritual evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.03,0:58:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,without an understanding of karma,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.03,0:58:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,because there's no explanation
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.03,0:58:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,for the seemingly negative
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.03,0:58:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,or the seemingly bizarre.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.03,0:58:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you go into past life recall,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.17,0:58:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and there are various techniques
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.17,0:58:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,which you can learn to do that
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.17,0:58:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,very simple self-hypnosis,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.17,0:58:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you can find out some of the things
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.17,0:58:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that are unexplainable in your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.17,0:58:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I spontaneously had such recalls
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.80,0:58:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and they were very, very vivid.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.80,0:58:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Very vivid.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.90,0:58:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like you remember something.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.90,0:58:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like you're watching a movie
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.19,0:58:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of something that happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.19,0:58:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,With past life recall,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.19,0:58:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens is the movie restarts
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.19,0:58:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're on stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.19,0:59:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not witnessing somebody's pain out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.32,0:59:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You're feeling it in your leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.32,0:59:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You really experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.32,0:59:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And suddenly what went on in that lifetime
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.32,0:59:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,makes complete sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.32,0:59:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see an exact connection
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.32,0:59:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,between an obligation.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.32,0:59:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So one of the reasons for spiritual work then
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.48,0:59:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is to speed up the evolution of karma,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.48,0:59:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,your karmic evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.48,0:59:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,To undo the negatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.48,0:59:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So how do we undo the negatives?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.48,0:59:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We undo the negatives by service to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.48,0:59:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,By modesty, humility,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.63,0:59:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,by goodwill and lovingness towards others.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.63,0:59:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So the traditional way is
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.96,0:59:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,by selfless service, karma yoga,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.96,0:59:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we undo the negatives by virtue of the positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.96,0:59:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The way it isn't so much we undo negative karma
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.25,0:59:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,as we overbalance it by creating good karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.25,0:59:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So traditionally in our culture then,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.38,0:59:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,karma yoga is not called karma yoga, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.38,1:00:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called volunteering.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.38,1:00:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Giving to the poor, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.38,1:00:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not called karma yoga.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.38,1:00:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But we know that selfless service,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.38,1:00:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,however it might be,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.38,1:00:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,it can be done in civil service.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.38,1:00:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be done in many ways.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.38,1:00:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So the last tool we need then
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.53,1:00:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to put it all together
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.53,1:00:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can remain rational, reasonable,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.53,1:00:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,educated and spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.53,1:00:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You need the understanding of karma,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.53,1:00:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the understanding of the calibrated levels
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.53,1:00:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.53,1:00:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when you tap that off
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.53,1:00:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,with devotion and commitment.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.53,1:00:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So all we need then to become enlightened
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.53,1:00:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is what we do at the beginning of the lecture.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.73,1:00:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We say,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.73,1:00:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Glory and excelsis to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.88,1:00:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We say,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.88,1:00:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All glory be to thee, O Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.88,1:00:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All glory be to thee, O Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.34,1:00:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That I may be of infinite service.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.98,1:00:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.38,1:00:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all we have to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.38,1:01:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the rest is up to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.38,1:01:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And the rest is up to the Holy Spirit.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.65,1:01:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And the rest is up to our good guides,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.65,1:01:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,our heavenly guides.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.73,1:01:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.73,1:01:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask about heavenly guides.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.78,1:01:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody has guardian angels.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.78,1:01:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.78,1:01:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the good news, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.57,1:01:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's got guardian angels.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.46,1:01:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Just some of you have pissed them off.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.46,1:01:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the only problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.94,1:01:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,My guardian angels are jokers.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.26,1:01:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, they tell me those things.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.26,1:01:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And I just say what they put in my mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.26,1:01:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They put it there.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.07,1:01:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't think that at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.07,1:01:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What time do we have to take a break?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.65,1:01:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We have about ten more minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.65,1:01:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.65,1:01:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.65,1:01:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.71,1:02:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.09,1:02:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that good news?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.09,1:02:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Does everybody know that you have guardian angels?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.09,1:02:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody think you don't have any spiritual guardian angels?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.09,1:02:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No skeptics?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.57,1:02:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the skeptics?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.65,1:02:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the rebellious adolescents?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.65,1:02:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.98,1:02:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.11,1:02:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was a teenager, there'd be all kinds of hands up.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.11,1:02:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Guardian angels.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.11,1:02:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, that's spooky stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.11,1:02:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't believe all that.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.11,1:02:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we do have guardian angels.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.78,1:02:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can learn to relate to them and pray to them.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.78,1:02:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And I always thank my guardian angels, you know, all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.86,1:02:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll say, thanks for that one.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.86,1:02:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Just missed the taxi cab.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.86,1:02:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Misses the pedestrian.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.86,1:02:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, whoops, thanks for that one.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.55,1:02:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,One time, I was a cab driver.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.55,1:02:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was approaching the main intersection of town at a great rate.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.07,1:03:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was going to break down right before the intersection.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.07,1:03:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And I stepped on the brake and the master cylinder went.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.07,1:03:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The cab careened madly through this crazy traffic and all these pedestrians.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.07,1:03:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And came to a rest quietly on the curb on the other side of the main drag, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.07,1:03:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what you call happy karmic consequence.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.48,1:03:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And the cop walked over to me and he said,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.48,1:03:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you just blew your master cylinder.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.15,1:03:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The guy actually knew.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.15,1:03:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, I mean, nobody would drive like that, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.15,1:03:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.15,1:03:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The cab actually said, you know, you just blew your master cylinder, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.26,1:03:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, the brake goes all the way down and there's nothing there.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.26,1:03:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But I could have killed many people.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.28,1:03:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I went right between all these people and didn't kill anybody or run over anybody, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.28,1:03:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if it isn't the guardian angel.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.28,1:03:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I mean, their guardian angels all got together.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.28,1:03:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And they gave me.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.28,1:03:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,A gang of them decided.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.17,1:04:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I never would have gotten through medical school otherwise, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.09,1:04:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we learn a lot then.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.30,1:04:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever we use consciousness calibration.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.30,1:04:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever we research what is the nature or the essence of things.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.30,1:04:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We always find out things that are helpful.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.30,1:04:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And each little piece of knowledge seems to fit in another brick in the wall, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.30,1:04:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like each one fits in and reinforces our overall understanding.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.30,1:04:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, we see all these great animals.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.36,1:04:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Over great periods of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.36,1:04:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of whom, as you know, are my favorites.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.36,1:04:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I love the octopus.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.36,1:04:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Komodo dragon.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.36,1:04:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And all those little friendly type creatures.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.84,1:04:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we notice, as we said, that the consciousness level of the animal kingdom is below 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.84,1:04:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And then suddenly you get to the herbivores.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.03,1:04:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see the carnivores.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.03,1:04:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The carnivores, they live by the death of others.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.03,1:04:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The carnivores.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.03,1:05:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The carnivores stays alive by the virtue of the death of others.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.03,1:05:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The dinosaur can't exist unless it eats, kills somebody.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.03,1:05:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And then at 200, we hit the herbivores.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.28,1:05:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the grazers.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.32,1:05:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The deer doesn't have to kill anybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.32,1:05:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The bison, the piggy, elk, dairy cow.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.32,1:05:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,None of these animals have to kill anybody in order to stay alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.44,1:05:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the cost of life then is the killing of innocent others, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.44,1:05:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The killing of others.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.44,1:05:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And then at level 200, consciousness evolves where we don't have to kill others to survive.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.57,1:05:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,A very significant jump in consciousness at consciousness level 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.57,1:05:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we'll move on to the next, yeah, three more minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.92,1:05:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The other, I'm putting together the pieces upon which the whole consciousness research is based.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.96,1:05:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The profound significance.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.96,1:05:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The profound significance in our culture.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.96,1:05:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm trying to emphasize the things that are of profound significance in our culture.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.96,1:06:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And the great books of the Western world are one of the, is the bricks in the wall of Western culture.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.21,1:06:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the erudition that has come about through the best thinking of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.21,1:06:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and reawakened from ancient Greece during the Reformation, during the Age of Enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.21,1:06:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And these are the great minds.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.21,1:06:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Which have shaped Western civilization.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.21,1:06:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Or the not so great minds which have threatened it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.21,1:06:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course Karl Marx.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.21,1:06:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Karl Marx at one level, level 130.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.25,1:06:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Then is dialectical materialism which exists now in new political clothes.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.25,1:06:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But still undermines all of the sanity of today's world.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.25,1:06:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are the great minds of all time.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.25,1:06:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,These were the books of my childhood.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.25,1:06:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Other people were reading comic books.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.25,1:07:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was reading the aphorisms of Marcus Aurelius.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.53,1:07:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was an oddball kid, as you can see.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.53,1:07:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Oddball kid.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.23,1:07:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than play football or baseball, I'd rather read the aphorisms of Marcus Aurelius.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.53,1:07:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so these, the great erudition was ancient Greece, ancient Athens.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.78,1:07:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The great minds of history.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.78,1:07:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, modern man is still struggling with things that were answered in the year 400.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.30,1:07:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The current political discourse is really rehashing things that have been solved for thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.61,1:07:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, one says, I see, the world I see is different than the world you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.01,1:07:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the argument which Plato answered.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.17,1:08:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The argument was, the world I see is a different world than the world you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.28,1:08:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So we live in different worlds.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.28,1:08:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That, of course, is fallacious.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.44,1:08:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It means, because your perception, what you're talking about is opinion.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.44,1:08:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And opinion is perception.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.44,1:08:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What a thing looks like is not its reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.43,1:08:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And what we've done with consciousness calibration, we've gone through what a thing looks like
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.43,1:08:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to find out the essence of what it really is.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.43,1:08:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So truth is based on essence, not on appearance.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.97,1:08:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And the way you can save yourself all kinds of trouble in buying the wrong stocks in the stock market, etc.,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.97,1:08:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is you can't go by appearance, you have to go by essence.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.97,1:08:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember all the glamour computer stocks.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.18,1:08:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember WorldCom and all them.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.18,1:08:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,People were shooting fortunes.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.52,1:08:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They were making fortunes overnight.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.52,1:08:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We calibrated them.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.61,1:08:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,They were 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.61,1:09:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,They were 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.61,1:09:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And Walmart was at 440.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.61,1:09:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So guess which one we bought stock in.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.61,1:09:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So people at that time politically were taking pot shots at Walmarts and buying WorldCom.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.75,1:09:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And I always said, well, that's not knowing perception from essence.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.93,1:09:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The perception is one thing and the essence is another, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.03,1:09:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we want to put our feet on
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.03,1:09:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is that which is truthful.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.03,1:09:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And the only way you can tell how truthful a thing is
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.03,1:09:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is by calibrating its level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.03,1:09:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are the great minds that have shaped all Western society.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.03,1:09:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And the collapse of these teachings in academia
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.32,1:09:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is why academia is currently falling at a rapid rate.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.32,1:09:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Current academia is calibrating below 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.42,1:09:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the end of that, she said.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.42,1:09:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We will take a break.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.57,1:10:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, dear.
